I'm a Resistance officer charged with overseeing the Dominion effort, and we're looking for a few good ${choice-player-gender}[men/women].
Since I don't see any around, it looks like you'll have to do.${prompt}
Ask about something?
${selection-lines}
Not now.
General information.
State of the Resistance.

Ask about something?
${selection-lines}
Not now.
The Dominion effort...?
How do I do my part?
What's in it for me?${prompt}
Wake up, soldier! I don't know if you're blind or stupid, but if you haven't noticed, there's a war going on around you.${prompt}
The Resistance is locked in a bitter struggle to take back our rightful land from the hordes, and secure a future for our kind.
We call this the Dominion effort. Has an inspiring ring to it, doesn't it, soldier?${prompt}
And if you haven't noticed, we don't exactly have a surplus of personnel.
Hell, I just got a field promotion from sergeant to tactician when my predecessor got his head lopped clean off by a fiend.
Now they've got some sissy boy doing my old job, but do you hear me complainin'?${prompt}
Anyhow, if you've got half a bloody stump of a leg to stand on and an arm to carry a blade, consider yourself recruited.
Now listen up, soldier, because I'm only going to say this once.${prompt}
I'll put this in terms even a dullard like you can understand.
The enemy we face consists of two types of fiends: nasty ones, and even nastier ones.${prompt}
We've got legions of ugly monsters prowling the land in throngs.
We cut them down, and lure their even nastier buddies out of hiding.${prompt}
These fiends are the beating heart of our enemy. Bring them down, and our battle is as good as won.
Get it? Good. Now hop to it, soldier!${prompt}
Hah! Ya may be short on wits, but you've got pluck.
There may be hope for you yet, soldier.${prompt}
If you're ready to make yourself useful, then you'll want to seek out one of our outposts.
There's three in the area, so even a rookie like yourself should be able to stumble upon one of 'em by dumb luck.${prompt}
Talk with a sergeant there, and sign up for one of our operations--Dominion Ops, we call 'em for short.
Each op will involve exterminating a prescribed quota of a particular variety of fiend.${prompt}
If you're halfway competent at your job, the Resistance will gradually expand its sphere of influence over the hordes.
Our ultimate goal is complete domination against all manner of fiends. That's one hundred percent, soldier!${prompt}
“What if I just kill fiends without signing up for ops,” you say?
Don't give me any of that lip, soldier!${prompt}
Listen. Every fiend you bring down will aid the cause.
But we can't be certain that we've achieved complete domination unless you sign up for ops, and report your success to the sergeant.
You'll also be rewarded for your efforts. Bet that got your interest quick, didn't it?${prompt}
There's more, soldier. This may sound bloody obvious--well, maybe not to a lackwit like you--but success in your efforts will raise the spirits of our entire company.${prompt}
With the resulting boost in morale, our troops will fight with even greater fervor, affording us all manner of advantages in battle.
“What kind of advantages?” Hah! That's for us to know and you to find out, soldier!${prompt}
Expand our sphere of influence over the peons, and we'll start to lure the big boys out of the woodwork.${prompt}
Take them out, and the biggest, baddest foes will start to show up.
Where does it all end, you say? It doesn't! This is war, soldier, not a Lightsday afternoon walk in the park!${prompt}
Now, where was I? The enemy leaders pack a punch, but they rely on their flunkies as the foundation for their strength.${prompt}
Cut their subordinates out from underneath them, and they won't have a leg--or gnarled, twisted appendage--to stand upon.
That's smart fighting. And in war, you fight smart or you die, soldier!${prompt}
I couldn't tell you how many of these buggers we're up against, but I do know this.
Each one we kill brings us closer to our goal of utter domination.${prompt}
To keep morale high, we can't let up the attack on the enemy leaders.
You got all that, soldier?${prompt}
What's in it for you?
You've got some nerve, soldier!${prompt}
You're here to follow orders, not question them!
When I say “jump,” you say “how many malms high, sir!?”
Are we understood, soldier!?${prompt}
But yeah, there's somethin' in it for you, if that's the only thing that's going to get you fighting for our cause instead of sitting around on your lazy backside.${prompt}
When you report back after completing an operation or successfully bring down a notorious foe, you'll be awarded remuneration in the form of something we call Dominion Notes.${prompt}
These notes can be exchanged for supplies to serve you on the field of battle: equipment, medicine, and more.
And we're not talking your run-of-the-mill items here. This is some impressive stuff. I daresay it's worth more than your life, soldier.${prompt}
Bet that put a spark in your eyes, didn't it?
What's more, bring back battle trophies--the severed heads and gore-stained limbs of the fiends you slay--and we will reward your accomplishments with guerdon.${prompt}
There are five echelons of trophies in total.
Slaying more powerful fiends will yield more prestigious trophies, which in turn will earn you more valuable guerdon.${prompt}
Battle trophies can even be exchanged for each other.
Multiple lower-echelon trophies can be upgraded to a single trophy of a higher echelon, or vice versa.
If you've got half a brain inside that skull of yours, you'll take advantage of this to obtain the guerdon you desire.${prompt}
The guerdon we offer consists of some of the richest spoils we've acquired in the course of the war--equipment augmented by powerful sorcery.
What manner of sorcery, you ask? That's classified information, soldier!${prompt}
And mind you, since they were magicked long before we got our hands on them, we have no way of altering the enchantment.
In other words, you'll take what we give you, and you'll thank us for it, soldier!${prompt}

Each Dominion Ops successfully completed slightly expands our sphere of influence over the Abyssean hordes.${prompt}
Needless to say, our ultimate goal is complete and utter domination. Every individual effort counts!${prompt}
